Movie: The Hunger Games: The Ballad of Songbirds & Snakes
The Killing of a Sacred Deer
Jeanne Dielman, 23, quai du Commerce, 1080 Bruxelles

Review: I watched this movie in high school and I have never stopped thinking about it; never stopped thinking about the story, the technique, the concept, but above all this bear. This baby cub brown bear that was the best actor I have seen in my life. The thoughts of this performance haunt me: He was an actual bear???? A baby bear???? And somehow showed complex emotion???? This bear was heartbroken, happy, also on shrooms for a portion of the film??…
